﻿Legal Disclaimer

The data and layers in these maps do not represent a survey. No accuracy is assumed for the data delineated herein, either expressed or implied by Kendall County or its employees.


These data are compiled from official records, including plats, surveys, recorded deeds, contracts, and only contains information required for local government purposes. See the recorded documents for more detailed legal information.﻿
Changelog

January 2022 | Version 2.2.1

Minor changes.

  • Property Information map includes basemap tool
  • Legislative Districts tab mobile/tablet views reconfigured for accessibility


January 2022 | Version 2.2

  • Voting tab now focuses on browsing the legislative districts. Voting lookup tool has been moved to own dedicated application


May 2021 | Version 2.1

  • Property Information tab no longer shows "1 of XXXX" with parcel / CAMA pre-selected. Only shows information upon selection.
  • Voting Lookup map also only shows info upon selection


﻿May 2021 | Version 2.0﻿

  • Renamed "Map Viewer" -- No more beta!
  • CAMA and Sales data can be spatially filtered and / or exported to CSV
  • Added tabs for Property Characteristics and Voting Information Lookup
  • Broke up the Guide into separate guides per page



﻿January 2021 | Version 1.2.1

  • Updated the Guide panel to address various updated features
  • Filter panel will appear by default in CAMA viewer
  • Adjustments to layer symbology



January 2021 | Version 1.2

  • Updated maps to be compliant with ArcGIS JavaScript API v 4.18
  • Added "Table View" to CAMA & Sales page



September 2020 | Version 1.1

  • Guide, changelog, and bugs list moved into side panel windows
  • Disclaimer appears as splash upon loading viewer
  • Published viewer to official URL


August 2020 | Version 1.0

  • Map Viewer officially released for public use
Known Issues﻿
• Print capability is missing﻿, but it's coming soon!﻿

config.text: ﻿Zoning Map Guide

This map displays zoning information and other related layers, such as flood zones, landuse, etc.


This map has a number of different tools and features available:


Layers and Legend

In the left panel, you will see a list of layers available in the map. By clicking the eye icon next to each layer, you can toggle them on and off.

Next to the layer list is a legend showing the currently visible layers and how they are represented in the map.


﻿Search

In the upper-left of the map, click the Search icon to expand the search bar. Begin typing, and the search tool will auto-suggest features that match your search.


Basemaps

Next to search icon is the Basemaps tool. This gives you the ability to toggle the basemap currently displayed.


There are a variety of maps available, from prior years' imagery to historic plat maps.


Measure

The last tool in the upper-left is the Measure tool. With this tool active, click on the map to begin drawing the line or area you wish to measure. Double-click to finish your drawing.


You can set the measurement units at any time; the label will automatically update to reflect your choice.


﻿Other Tips

The side panel can be re-sized by clicking and dragging divider bar. This can help adjust the app to your screen size.
﻿CAMA and Sales Guide

﻿This map gives users more advanced capabilities for browsing / filtering property characteristics and recent sales.


This map has a number of different tools and features available:


Filters

The panel to the left gives users the ability to filter the data currently displayed in the CAMA and Sales layers.


Table View

Above the map, there are two tabs. Use these to switch between the default map view and a table-based view of the data.


Note that applying filters will apply to both the map and the table.


From the table, users can also export features to a CSV file by clicking the icon in the upper-right of the table.


﻿Search

In the upper-left of the map, click the Search icon to expand the search bar. Begin typing, and the search tool will auto-suggest features that match your search.


You can search by:

  • PIN (with or without hyphens)
  • Site Address
  • Current Owner
  • Grantor / Grantee (Sales)


Layers

Next to the search icon is the Layers tool. Use this tool to turn the map layers on and off as needed, or to view the legend for the visible layers.


Basemaps

Next to layers icon is the Basemaps tool. This gives you the ability to toggle the basemap currently displayed.


There are a variety of maps available, from prior years' imagery to historic plat maps.


Measure

The last tool in the upper-left is the Measure tool. With this tool active, click on the map to begin drawing the line or area you wish to measure. Double-click to finish your drawing.


You can set the measurement units at any time; the label will automatically update to reflect your choice.


﻿Other Tips

The side panel can be re-sized by clicking and dragging divider bar. This can help adjust the app to your screen size.
﻿Property Information Guide

﻿This map is meant to make it as easy as possible to look up information about parcels and structures.


To get information, do either of the following:


A) Click on a Parcel

It's really that easy! Just click on a parcel in the map and the information panels will update.


B) Search for a Parcel

Click the Search icon in the upper-left of the map to expand the search bar. As you type, the search bar will auto-suggest possible matches based on what you enter.


You can search by:

  • PIN (with or without hyphens!)
  • Site Address


Other Tips

The side panel can be re-sized by clicking and dragging divider bar. This can help adjust the app to your screen size.


Next to the search widget, you can click on the Basemap tool to change the map's background.
Legislative District Browser Guide

Use this map to view the various legislative districts in Kendall County.


Left Side Panel: Layer List

On the left-hand side, users can find a list of the different layers in the map. Clicking the eye icon will toggle each layer on and off.


Next to the layer list is a legend, showing what the various symbols in the map refer to.


The Map

In the center of the screen is the map. This shows all active layers. You can search for specific parcels or addresses using the map's search tool, or just navigate the map as you do elsewhere.


Parcel-Specific Information

Click a parcel to view information about the precinct, polling place, and any legislative districts to which the parcel is assigned, as well as a few other key details about the property.


Right Panel

At the right side of the screen are several lists of the different legislative districts in the county, separated by type. Clicking any of these will display it prominently on the map, as well as move the map to the feature's location.


If the map is zoomed in too far to see the district, simply click the Home button to return to the full county extent.


Note: legislative district features have been clipped to the boundary of the county.﻿
Explore Map Guide

The "Explore" map is meant to allow more in-depth, interactive access to the Tax Map features (parcels, lots, etc.), as well as other important layers.


This map has a number of different tools and features available:


﻿Search

In the upper-left of the map, click the Search icon to expand the search bar. Begin typing, and the search tool will auto-suggest features that match your search.


You can search for:

  • PIN (with and without hyphens)
  • Address
  • Subdivision / Condominium Name


Layers

Next to the search tool is the Layers icon. This will show you the list of layers available in the map. Clicking the eye icon next to each layer can turn it on and off.


You can also toggle the layer list to the Legend view to see how each layer is symbolized.


Basemaps

Next to the layer list is the Basemaps tool. This gives you the ability to toggle the basemap currently displayed.


There are a variety of maps available, from prior years' imagery to historic plat maps.


Measure

The last tool in the upper-left is the Measure tool. With this tool active, click on the map to begin drawing the line or area you wish to measure. Double-click to finish your drawing.


You can set the measurement units at any time; the label will automatically update to reflect your choice.


Tax Map Experience

In the lower-left of the map, there is a thumbnail of another map. Click on this to switch the current map for a predefined "Tax Map" view. This map attempts to replicate the appearance of a cadastral tax map.


Click the thumbnail again to switch back.

About
﻿About

﻿This web application attempts to provide a single location for many of the more popular viewers, layers, and tools that our users have come to rely upon.


Use the tabs / menu button at the top of the page to navigate between the different tools. If you are unsure of how to use a particular tool, each page has its own guide panel that you can reference.


We will continue to develop this application as new capabilities become available or are requested. User feedback is a crucial element to that process, and we welcome any constructive comments you may have.


Please note! Though we attempt to make this application adaptable to tablet and mobile devices, use of a full-size screen is recommended for best results.
